1
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:54,040
Oh, where did it go?

2
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:20,240
Pin.

3
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:27,520
You can't harm the animals.

4
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:30,880
If I shoot you,
you'll feel hurt too, right?

5
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,480
These are just rubber bullets.

6
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:33,400
They won't die.

7
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:34,360
What'd you say?

8
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:36,240
Jom, don't.

9
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:40,360
- Hey.
- No. Please don't.

10
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:44,440
No, don't shoot. Please. Please don't.

11
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:45,680
You won't die, right?

12
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:46,760
Then why are you afraid?

13
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:50,880
Stop harming the defenseless animals.

14
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:53,200
And if you're upset with me,

15
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:54,840
here's my name tag.

16
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:56,800
Go ahead and tell the farm owner.

17
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,840
I'll testify for you.

18
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:05,360
You're not in the wrong.

19
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:06,880
But he's a customer.

20
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:09,600
There's nothing I can do
if he decides to report me.

21
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:20,560
I'm sorry.

22
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:24,520
You're so cool.

23
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:40,200
I'll take care of this.

24
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,640
Go treat your wound.

25
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,880
I'm fine, Jom.

26
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:47,280
I want to make this farm
as beautiful and perfect as possible,

27
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,600
before…

28
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:02,600
Jom. Look at that.

29
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:13,200
What is it, Pin? I don't see anything.

30
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:46,800
Paisal Farm is still
as big and magnificent as ever.

31
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:48,840
<i>So what are you gonna do?</i>

32
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:50,680
<i>The deadline's almost here.</i>

33
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:54,560
<i>If you don't do anything,</i>
<i>you'll lose it all.</i>

34
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,840
Get here quickly.

35
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:02,120
We're arming the explosive.

36
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:03,240
Prepare for the countdown.

37
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:07,560
Finally,

38
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:12,400
we get to meet, Pinanong.

39
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:10,320
We're about to see each other,

40
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:12,200
Mr. Na.

41
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:28,160
The tree looks strong.

42
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:30,000
It doesn't need to be fertilized.

43
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:34,760
Well, the owner is coming back,

44
00:07:34,840 --> 00:07:37,440
and I want to nurture it,
so the flowers bloom.

45
00:07:40,840 --> 00:07:42,440
Here, I'll do it.

46
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:53,960
I hope you get struck by lightning
and break into pieces.

47
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:04,280
Oh? Jom? Jom.

48
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,440
Pin!

49
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:08,800
Here you are. I was looking all over.

50
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:09,800
What's wrong, Noi?

51
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:11,320
Aunt Un is in trouble.

52
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:12,800
Did someone do something to Mom?

53
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:16,160
It was Madam. Madam…

54
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:22,320
Please believe me.

55
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:24,160
I don't have that much money.

56
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:27,920
I just used it for groceries,
and now, it's all gone.

57
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,520
If you're out of cash, Pin must have some.

58
00:08:31,760 --> 00:08:33,760
She gave me her whole salary.

59
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:35,440
She really doesn't have any left.

60
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:37,240
But I have to give him the money.

61
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,919
If I don't, I'm dead.

62
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,520
Do you want to see me die?

63
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:42,960
Enough, please.

64
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:44,720
Don't go to that place ever again.

65
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,560
It will only ruin your life.

66
00:08:46,640 --> 00:08:47,960
How dare you lecture me.

67
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:49,120
Ugh.

68
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,360
And what is this?

69
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:57,240
Didn't you say you had nothing of value?

70
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,920
- So what is this?
- Please don't take it.

71
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:02,160
It is the only thing of value
Mr. Paisal gave us when Pin was born.

72
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:03,600
Please don't take it.

73
00:09:03,680 --> 00:09:05,760
- Between this bracelet
- Please.

74
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:08,440
and my life, which is more important?

75
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:32,880
- Madam.
- Move. I'm in a hurry. Move!

76
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:35,840
Mom.

77
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:46,000
Mom.

78
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,120
Uh…

79
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:49,800
What was that all about?

80
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:54,080
Mom. Are you hurt?

81
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:56,840
I already told you I'm fine.

82
00:09:56,920 --> 00:10:00,040
I just stepped on something and slipped.

83
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:04,280
No. I heard Madam was digging through
Aunt Un's things, looking for money.

84
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:08,760
Hey, stop talking nonsense.

85
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:10,600
Your ears are looking for trouble.

86
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:13,560
Madam was only looking
for some old photos,

87
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:15,360
and I was just helping her.

88
00:10:16,560 --> 00:10:18,280
She has plenty of money.

89
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:20,640
Why would she bother taking anything
from a maid?

90
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:24,560
But she hasn't paid any of us
for two or three months now.

91
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:26,240
Doesn't that mean she's broke?

92
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:28,440
Hey. Well…

93
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:31,000
She has a massive farm to manage.

94
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:33,440
Sometimes, the cash flow is tight.

95
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:38,800
Since Mr. Paisal passed away,
she has been managing it all alone.

96
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:42,000
And she still has
to cover Mr. Na's tuition.

97
00:10:42,760 --> 00:10:44,760
- Aunt Un. But it's--
- Noi…

98
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:47,800
Fine.

99
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:53,880
Oh, right. Madam told us
to tidy up Mr. Na's room, right?

100
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:56,040
Is everything alright? Is it done?

101
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:57,400
I need to take a look.

102
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:58,600
Uh…

103
00:10:58,680 --> 00:11:02,240
Mom, don't worry. I already handled it.

104
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:03,840
There are still some items missing.

105
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:06,600
But I still have some money left
from selling things online.

106
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:08,480
I can cover the cost.

107
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:11,400
Alright.

108
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:28,960
Seems like bananas alone
aren't tasty enough.

109
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:31,960
Put his hand down there.

110
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:35,360
- Come here.
- No! Don't! Sir, please!

111
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:36,960
- Move!
- Please, sir! Please!

112
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:42,720
Here. The interest I owe you.

113
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:44,000
Let my man go.

114
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:48,840
I'll pay the rest in installments.

115
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,200
Let him go.

116
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,440
Wait.

117
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:04,640
I see you kept your word.

118
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:09,160
You're a reliable debtor, so I'll give you
some capital back to try your luck again.

119
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:11,520
That way, you'll be able
to pay off all the debt.

120
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,680
No need for monthly installments.

121
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:14,960
It's a waste of time.

122
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:24,640
I'm Thai.

123
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:29,320
Oh, you're Thai? So let's speak Thai.

124
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:32,800
Where would you like to go, ma'am?

125
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:36,040
Paisal Farm, please.

126
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:39,600
Oh. Hop in.

127
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:43,720
Come on. Let me help. Get in.

128
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:44,880
It's okay.

129
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:50,000
Uh, I called someone at the farm.

130
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:51,240
He's coming to pick me up.

131
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:54,080
Huh? Then why did you even hail a ride?

132
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:56,560
What a waste of my time.

133
00:14:57,280 --> 00:14:58,320
I'm sorry.

134
00:14:59,000 --> 00:14:59,840
Ugh.

135
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:21,640
Uncle Win, I was just about to call you.

136
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:23,120
Can you come pick me up?

137
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:25,080
I can't find a ride home.

138
00:15:25,160 --> 00:15:26,040
Oh, Noi?

139
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:29,400
Mom passed out?

140
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:32,600
Can Uncle Win take her to the hospital?

141
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:36,000
What about Jom?

142
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:39,640
Okay. I'll hurry back.

143
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:04,120
Wow. Looks like no one's coming, ma'am.

144
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:13,400
Hey, why are you taking my stuff?

145
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:17,040
Hey. Put them down,
or I'll call the police.

146
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:20,680
Ugh. Don't you know, ma'am?

147
00:16:20,760 --> 00:16:22,320
Ever since COVID,

148
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:24,640
cab and tuk-tuk drivers
have all changed jobs.

149
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:29,080
Besides, this area
isn't exactly a tourist hotspot.

150
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:30,760
If I weren't such a nice guy,

151
00:16:30,840 --> 00:16:33,960
I would have gone home
to my wife and kids by now.

152
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:01,120
Hey, could you please slow down?

153
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:07,480
Hey, can you hear me? I said slow down.

154
00:17:11,119 --> 00:17:13,680
Hey, slow down.

155
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:15,440
Ugh. Hey!

156
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:18,400
Hey. Why are we turning here?

157
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:20,160
You were supposed to go straight.

158
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:23,760
Hey! Make a U-turn now! Turn around!

159
00:17:23,839 --> 00:17:25,000
- Whoo!
- Uh.

160
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:30,520
Sorry, sorry. My bad.

161
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:32,080
What did you say just now?

162
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:34,200
You took a wrong turn.

163
00:17:34,280 --> 00:17:36,160
Paisal Farm is back that way.

164
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:40,040
Oh. There's roadwork going on that way.

165
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:41,880
We need to take a detour here.

166
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:43,160
- Huh?
- Mm.

167
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:44,400
No, there's no roadwork.

168
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:48,840
I passed by there late this morning,
and the road was fine. Turn around.

169
00:17:51,440 --> 00:17:52,600
Turn around.

170
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:56,720
Okay, okay. Customer's always right, huh.

171
00:18:08,840 --> 00:18:09,880
- Hey.
- What's going on?

172
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,960
I said turn around and go back that way.

173
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:13,200
Turn around now.

174
00:18:13,280 --> 00:18:14,640
Ugh.

175
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:16,960
Turn around, will you?

176
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:19,520
Ugh, maybe this tuk-tuk
didn't like the yelling.

177
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:20,440
It just died on us.

178
00:18:21,080 --> 00:18:25,000
So… let me resuscitate it real quick.

179
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:08,000
Bad news.

180
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:12,240
The engine's fine, but the tank's empty.

181
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:14,640
Keep an eye on the tuk-tuk
while I go get some gas.

182
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:17,040
Hey, wait. What about…

183
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:18,200
Hey!

184
00:20:09,360 --> 00:20:10,960
Where are you running off to?

185
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:14,240
Hey. Don't come closer.

186
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:17,840
Don't mess around with anything sharp.

187
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:19,440
The spirits will cause accidents.

188
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:22,880
I work for Paisal Farm.

189
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:26,960
Madam Krongsuk, the owner,
has friends in very high places.

190
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:30,040
If something happens to me,
your family will be in trouble.

191
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:33,440
I know some officers too.

192
00:20:33,520 --> 00:20:38,320
We're tight. We go way back to my time
in Klong Prem, Bang Kwang, and Lat Yao.

193
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:40,800
You have a family.

194
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:43,320
Why don't you just do honest work?

195
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:45,760
You know how upset they'd be
if they found out?

196
00:20:47,760 --> 00:20:49,400
Oh, I'm moved to tears.

197
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:52,920
You must have talked
so many thieves out of their lifestyle.

198
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:56,080
Gorgeous, if you'd only love me,
I'd leave my wife.

199
00:20:56,160 --> 00:20:58,760
Come here. Hey, wait. Hey.

200
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:06,400
I told you not to come closer!

201
00:21:20,560 --> 00:21:21,920
You made me bleed?

202
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:39,880
- Pin!
- Jin?

203
00:21:41,320 --> 00:21:42,920
- Jin.
- What are you doing out here?

204
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:46,120
A robber! I'm being chased by a robber.

205
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,640
We need to get away. Let's go.

206
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:50,960
Hurry.

207
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:21,280
Mom. Mom.

208
00:22:22,760 --> 00:22:23,840
Why isn't she here?

209
00:22:24,880 --> 00:22:28,120
Could Noi have already taken Aunt Un
to the hospital?

210
00:22:29,080 --> 00:22:30,480
What's happening? What is it?

211
00:22:30,560 --> 00:22:31,960
Who's going to the hospital?

212
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:32,960
Mom.

213
00:22:35,840 --> 00:22:39,160
What's wrong? Hey, I can't breathe.

214
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:41,600
Noi said you had passed out.

215
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:43,040
Pin was panicking.

216
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:48,480
Noi has always been an alarmist.

217
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:50,640
It was nothing.

218
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:54,640
I was reaching up and down, taking off
the curtains from the main house to wash,

219
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:58,160
and I felt lightheaded,
just as older people sometimes feel.

220
00:22:58,240 --> 00:23:00,440
And why did you have to do that yourself?

221
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:02,960
I told you I'd take them
to the laundromat myself.

222
00:23:03,760 --> 00:23:05,680
Why take them to the laundromat?

223
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:06,600
That's a waste of money.

224
00:23:06,680 --> 00:23:08,000
Are you rich or something?

225
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:10,400
Should we check your blood pressure?

226
00:23:10,480 --> 00:23:12,360
I've got a device in the car.

227
00:23:13,560 --> 00:23:15,240
It's okay. There's no need.

228
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:18,760
Oh, so where's all the stuff?

229
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:21,160
Didn't you go
to get things ready for Mr. Na?

230
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:22,560
I'm not seeing anything.

231
00:23:25,840 --> 00:23:28,360
I've got the shop delivering them
to us later.

232
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:29,760
There was too much stuff.

233
00:23:45,160 --> 00:23:46,800
You're really not going to file a report?

234
00:23:46,880 --> 00:23:50,880
What are you going to do about the stuff
and important docs in your bag?

235
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:52,680
It was just my ID card.

236
00:23:52,760 --> 00:23:55,240
I'll just report it as missing
and get a new one.

237
00:23:55,320 --> 00:23:57,680
My ATM card barely has any cash anyway.

238
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:59,200
Might as well terminate the account,

239
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:01,120
or it'll be too much trouble.

240
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:04,480
But Pin, that lunatic
will just go on to rob someone else.

241
00:24:05,560 --> 00:24:07,800
I just don't want
Mom and Madam to find out.

242
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:10,720
There's already enough trouble here.

243
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:16,120
Then there is a problem here,
just like everyone's been saying.

244
00:24:16,200 --> 00:24:17,720
What are they saying?

245
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:26,480
<i>Since Mr. Paisal's death,</i>

246
00:24:28,320 --> 00:24:31,840
<i>Madam has been spending recklessly,</i>
<i>with no regard for the farm.</i>

247
00:24:31,920 --> 00:24:34,880
<i>She is drowning in debt,</i>
<i>yet she maintains a lavish lifestyle</i>

248
00:24:34,960 --> 00:24:36,760
<i>and pays for her nephew to study abroad.</i>

249
00:24:36,840 --> 00:24:38,440
<i>And there's another rumor.</i>

250
00:24:38,960 --> 00:24:40,560
<i>This one's quite shocking.</i>

251
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:42,160
<i>I'm not sure if you've heard it.</i>

252
00:24:42,960 --> 00:24:47,800
Madam has been trying
to sell the farm, but she can't

253
00:24:47,880 --> 00:24:50,280
because she's afraid
the true heir will reclaim it.

254
00:25:07,640 --> 00:25:09,080
Wait for me, alright?

255
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:14,240
Don't date anyone else.

256
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:43,240
Take good care of our Indian Cork tree.

257
00:25:55,640 --> 00:25:58,320
I'll wait for only you, Mr. Na.

258
00:26:26,360 --> 00:26:28,520
Mom. Mom!

259
00:26:30,600 --> 00:26:33,880
Mom. Mom.

260
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:36,880
Mom. Mom.

261
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:07,960
Yai, where the hell have you been?

262
00:27:08,560 --> 00:27:10,080
I called you a million times.

263
00:27:10,680 --> 00:27:13,200
What? I was only gone
for a couple of hours.

264
00:27:13,280 --> 00:27:15,680
Were you missing me that much, bestie?

265
00:27:16,280 --> 00:27:19,560
I don't give a damn how you are.

266
00:27:20,120 --> 00:27:22,960
But if something happened to you,

267
00:27:23,040 --> 00:27:24,640
you know who would come after me.

268
00:27:29,840 --> 00:27:31,760
And what is this, huh?

269
00:27:31,840 --> 00:27:33,280
The stuff I robbed.

270
00:27:34,040 --> 00:27:35,800
Ah. Huh?

271
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:49,560
Hello, Aunt Pen.

272
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:52,320
Mr. Yai's back.

273
00:27:53,080 --> 00:27:54,040
<i>It's too late.</i>

274
00:27:54,120 --> 00:27:56,960
Pload's bringing his men
to Paisal Farm now.

275
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:02,560
- Here's your gun, Boss.
- Get the arms ready.

276
00:28:05,080 --> 00:28:07,200
It's time to finally
settle the score with them.

277
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:11,840
Crap. Aunt Pen.

278
00:28:11,920 --> 00:28:14,200
Can you tell Dad to calm down?

279
00:28:14,720 --> 00:28:16,200
This isn't a war movie.

280
00:28:16,280 --> 00:28:17,800
We live in a country with laws.

281
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:21,040
Mr. Yai. We're screwed.

282
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:22,920
Dad's bringing his men here.

283
00:28:26,840 --> 00:28:29,800
Pload. Pload, wait.

284
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:32,680
Here. Listen.

285
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:35,400
Uncle Pload.

286
00:28:37,040 --> 00:28:38,760
Huh? Mr. Yai?

287
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:41,400
Take it easy, Uncle. I'm okay.

288
00:28:41,480 --> 00:28:44,440
I went out to gather some intel
but didn't tell Pan.

289
00:28:44,520 --> 00:28:45,920
It was urgent.

290
00:28:46,760 --> 00:28:50,440
Mr. Yai, don't ever be too careless.

291
00:28:50,520 --> 00:28:53,560
Those people are all dangerous.

292
00:28:54,480 --> 00:28:58,640
If there's any trouble,
let me know right away.

293
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:01,080
No need to get your hands dirty.

294
00:29:01,600 --> 00:29:03,680
I can manage this on my own.

295
00:29:03,760 --> 00:29:06,480
Don't forget that
I've learned everything from you,

296
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:09,920
and I have Pan,
a top-tier legal counselor, by my side.

297
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:12,160
I won't go down easily.

298
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:14,000
Mr. Yai, but…

299
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:18,280
Mr. Yai?

300
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:24,880
See? I told you
that you were just being impatient.

301
00:29:27,040 --> 00:29:30,680
That's because I know very well
how vicious they are.

302
00:29:31,920 --> 00:29:35,400
I won't let Mr. Yai
lose to them ever again.

303
00:29:40,680 --> 00:29:41,520
Hey.

304
00:29:41,600 --> 00:29:44,000
You said you robbed someone. Who was it?

305
00:29:44,080 --> 00:29:45,560
Or were you just kidding?

306
00:29:45,640 --> 00:29:46,640
I was serious.

307
00:29:47,560 --> 00:29:50,920
I set out to steal
someone's heart, but I failed.

308
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:52,320
- Eh?
- Let's go.

309
00:29:53,320 --> 00:29:56,560
Yai. Yai, where are we going?

310
00:30:02,840 --> 00:30:04,040
What a shame.

311
00:30:04,120 --> 00:30:05,440
You should have stopped after you won.

312
00:30:05,520 --> 00:30:06,720
We're in the red again.

313
00:30:06,800 --> 00:30:08,760
And you think complaining will help?

314
00:30:08,840 --> 00:30:11,040
We're lucky enough
that Mr. Tong let us leave.

315
00:30:11,120 --> 00:30:12,680
There's always next time.

316
00:30:14,240 --> 00:30:16,560
What about
the almost a million baht we owe him?

317
00:30:17,440 --> 00:30:18,960
Can you not ask me right now?

318
00:30:19,040 --> 00:30:21,960
I have no idea. I'm tired. Just drive.

319
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:23,840
Ugh.

320
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:39,640
The private investigator said that
this gambling den is run by Mr. Tong,

321
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:44,240
a big shot the police won't touch
until he slips up on a drug charge.

322
00:30:45,760 --> 00:30:47,800
Krongsuk has been
a regular here for some time.

323
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:52,680
Interesting.

324
00:30:54,080 --> 00:30:56,600
Hey, Yai. Where do you think you're going?

325
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:59,360
I want to take a gamble for once.

326
00:30:59,440 --> 00:31:01,280
Hey. Get back here, Yai.

327
00:31:02,680 --> 00:31:05,320
Yai. Where are you going, Yai?

328
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:06,640
Ugh.

329
00:31:23,480 --> 00:31:25,800
Is my mom's condition serious?

330
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:28,120
She needs to undergo
a balloon angioplasty.

331
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:30,080
Please sign the consent form.

332
00:31:30,160 --> 00:31:31,000
Here.

333
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:34,480
Pin.

334
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:35,920
- Can I take a look?
- Yes.

335
00:31:40,320 --> 00:31:42,640
Pin. You need to sign it.

336
00:32:15,040 --> 00:32:17,280
It's time to go all-in.

337
00:32:24,560 --> 00:32:26,640
Triple Aces.

338
00:32:39,600 --> 00:32:41,160
I've got triple Aces too.

339
00:32:46,600 --> 00:32:48,360
Hey, how is that possible?

340
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:51,840
There are only four Aces in a deck.

341
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:53,440
How come you've got triple Aces?

342
00:32:53,520 --> 00:32:54,440
Search him!

343
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:57,800
Hey, wait, wait. Easy. Calm down.

344
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:07,720
Must have been a mix-up at the laundromat.

345
00:33:07,800 --> 00:33:09,400
I seem to have the magician's jacket.

346
00:33:09,480 --> 00:33:10,600
Beat him up.

347
00:33:23,880 --> 00:33:26,280
Put all the money in this bag
if you want to live.

348
00:33:27,040 --> 00:33:29,560
Now! Faster!

349
00:33:30,160 --> 00:33:31,640
Faster, fatso!

350
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:34,080
Faster!

351
00:33:35,960 --> 00:33:38,280
- Faster, fatso!
- Calm down, bro.

352
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:43,200
Easy. Easy.

353
00:33:43,280 --> 00:33:45,040
Follow me if you wanna die!

354
00:33:46,960 --> 00:33:48,440
Get up and follow him!

355
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:57,360
- Hey!
- There he is!

356
00:33:59,000 --> 00:33:59,960
Chase him!

357
00:34:03,160 --> 00:34:04,200
Stop!

358
00:34:06,240 --> 00:34:07,240
Hey!

359
00:34:15,480 --> 00:34:16,400
Hey!

360
00:34:17,639 --> 00:34:20,760
Huh? Where's Pan gone?

361
00:34:34,560 --> 00:34:36,000
Go!

362
00:34:36,880 --> 00:34:38,040
Where did Pan go?

363
00:34:41,360 --> 00:34:43,880
- Pan!
- Hey, get in, Yai.

364
00:34:45,719 --> 00:34:48,360
- Where have you been? That was close.
- Just get in.

365
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:50,320
Your timing is absolute shit.

366
00:34:58,400 --> 00:35:00,040
What the hell did you do, Yai?

367
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:03,240
I brought you here to try the bullets!

368
00:35:06,560 --> 00:35:08,320
Yai, you bastard.

369
00:35:14,600 --> 00:35:16,080
Come on.

370
00:35:40,240 --> 00:35:41,640
- Yai…
- Whoo!

371
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:43,800
What a blast!

372
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:47,680
Would you like to go
to Heaven or Hell, Mr. Yai?

373
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:49,280
Tell me where to go!

374
00:35:49,880 --> 00:35:51,760
- Paisal Farm.
- Huh?

375
00:35:52,640 --> 00:35:54,120
Why would you go there?

376
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:56,360
This is not part of the plan.

377
00:35:58,240 --> 00:36:00,760
Hey, slow down. Don't go too fast.

378
00:36:00,840 --> 00:36:01,880
They won't catch up.

379
00:36:01,960 --> 00:36:03,120
What are you talking about?

380
00:36:03,200 --> 00:36:05,040
They're gonna kill us!

381
00:36:15,320 --> 00:36:16,360
Faster.

382
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:29,720
Here they come. Keep this distance.

383
00:36:29,800 --> 00:36:31,960
Distance, my ass.

384
00:36:32,040 --> 00:36:33,520
Those are bullets, you idiot.

385
00:36:38,880 --> 00:36:40,040
Oh. Whoa.

386
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:47,240
We're almost there.

387
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:48,200
You want me to go inside?

388
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:51,280
No, drive past it and drop me off nearby.

389
00:36:51,360 --> 00:36:52,360
Then you can go home.

390
00:36:53,200 --> 00:36:55,760
Tell me what exactly
you're planning to do first.

391
00:36:57,440 --> 00:36:59,360
And where's the fun in that?

392
00:37:00,480 --> 00:37:01,600
Yai.

393
00:37:03,520 --> 00:37:05,640
Ugh. You do this every single time.

394
00:37:08,920 --> 00:37:10,440
Hey, I said go faster!

395
00:37:22,960 --> 00:37:24,080
Pan, slow down.

396
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:27,120
Hey, Yai!

397
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:34,560
You madman. Ugh.

398
00:37:44,600 --> 00:37:46,720
No criminal would dare
set foot on our farm.

399
00:37:47,720 --> 00:37:49,480
And you're not the police.

400
00:37:50,720 --> 00:37:54,640
If you want to enter the farm,
you'll have to get through us first.

401
00:38:02,920 --> 00:38:04,320
What did you call me over for?

402
00:38:05,640 --> 00:38:09,160
They said they know the manager and want
to come inside to look for a robber.

403
00:38:15,760 --> 00:38:16,960
Oh, we know each other.

404
00:38:18,440 --> 00:38:19,680
What happened?

405
00:38:47,680 --> 00:38:49,320
What took you so long?

406
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:52,000
I thought the nurse said
Aunt Un was being discharged soon.

407
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:55,720
I just spoke
with their billing department.

408
00:38:56,480 --> 00:38:58,240
The angioplasty costs 300,000 baht.

409
00:38:58,960 --> 00:38:59,920
Huh?

410
00:39:01,560 --> 00:39:04,240
But this is a public hospital.

411
00:39:04,320 --> 00:39:06,080
Isn't she eligible
for free medical treatment?

412
00:39:06,160 --> 00:39:08,480
My mom doesn't have ID card.

413
00:39:09,120 --> 00:39:10,800
I've tried everything I can,

414
00:39:10,880 --> 00:39:12,920
but the district office
wouldn't issue her one.

415
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:15,440
They insisted that she find
some relatives and get some DNA tests.

416
00:39:15,520 --> 00:39:16,360
But…

417
00:39:17,440 --> 00:39:20,160
But Mom doesn't even know
who her real parents are.

418
00:40:22,800 --> 00:40:24,240
Help!

419
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:33,480
This is the maids' quarters.

420
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:35,000
There should be nothing here.

421
00:40:35,800 --> 00:40:36,760
Let's go.

422
00:40:45,920 --> 00:40:48,120
Gorgeous, if you snitch
and tell them I'm here,

423
00:40:48,680 --> 00:40:51,680
I'll just tell them
we were busy making love.

424
00:40:51,760 --> 00:40:54,040
We were doing it so passionately.

425
00:41:10,400 --> 00:41:11,400
Call them out there.

426
00:41:11,480 --> 00:41:12,560
I want to look inside.

427
00:41:18,840 --> 00:41:19,680
Pin.

428
00:41:25,160 --> 00:41:26,000
Mr. Teera?

429
00:41:27,680 --> 00:41:29,680
Do you need anything?

430
00:41:29,760 --> 00:41:32,160
I'm about to take a shower.

431
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:37,200
We're searching for a robber.
Let me look inside.

432
00:41:37,800 --> 00:41:40,800
- Hey, hey. I think that's…
- Hey. Search for him.

433
00:41:47,520 --> 00:41:48,760
Uh.

434
00:42:12,560 --> 00:42:14,400
There's nothing but clothing in there.

435
00:42:17,920 --> 00:42:20,200
Uh, if any of my valuables go missing,

436
00:42:20,280 --> 00:42:21,880
I'll call the police.

437
00:42:32,440 --> 00:42:35,360
Uh… That's my phone.

438
00:42:45,880 --> 00:42:47,840
I don't think he came in here.

439
00:42:48,360 --> 00:42:49,600
Let's check the back of the farm.

440
00:42:52,560 --> 00:42:53,520
Hey.

441
00:43:08,440 --> 00:43:09,600
Are you scared, Pin?

442
00:43:16,040 --> 00:43:18,720
It's fine now. I'll go.

443
00:43:35,320 --> 00:43:36,960
<i>Go ahead and tuck yourself in.</i>

444
00:43:37,040 --> 00:43:38,560
<i>I'll be in touch.</i>

445
00:43:55,680 --> 00:43:59,160
Oh, go take a shower if you want.

446
00:43:59,240 --> 00:44:01,400
I'm just gonna lie here for a while.

447
00:44:01,480 --> 00:44:04,520
It's not often that
I come across a bed this soft.

448
00:44:18,400 --> 00:44:20,480
<i>Was it you who took the truck</i>
<i>and tried to steal the sheep?</i>

449
00:44:20,560 --> 00:44:22,720
Who would waste time
stealing their own property?

450
00:44:24,200 --> 00:44:25,440
What the hell does that mean?

451
00:44:25,520 --> 00:44:27,760
Foul language? So we're close now?

452
00:44:28,800 --> 00:44:32,680
<i>Did that catch you off guard,</i>
<i>my beloved stepmother?</i>

453
00:44:33,280 --> 00:44:34,520
Don't shoot.

454
00:44:35,120 --> 00:44:36,400
<i>What is this all about, Noi?</i>

455
00:44:36,480 --> 00:44:38,560
<i>Earlier, he was a robber.</i>

456
00:44:38,640 --> 00:44:41,480
But now he's the heir to Paisal Farm!

457
00:44:42,200 --> 00:44:43,640
Mr. Yai came back?

458
00:45:23,120 --> 00:45:25,320
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
